<br>
I'd first just add a general purpose set of dd and aoe for wizards and mages that are a solid 25 %(wiz) and 15 %(mage) more efficient than they currently have and leave druid nukes as they are, this would put wizards way out in front with mages not TOO far behind them. Then I would add a screaming terror type mez and a 1500 point heal with a pretty fast cast time and relatively low mana cost to druids (though not as low as torpor.) And boom, casters are pretty much balanced.<br>
<br>
As far as balancing casters vs melee, I would think that a combo of increasing meditation rates a bit and lowering some mobs resists would handle that.<br>
<br>
Please post your ideas too<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Keep in mind the purpose is overall caster balance, not just  &quot;fixing druids cause we suck&quot; hehe.<br>
<br>
Mine focusses on the 3 classes who really need to be brought up to par the most. I think these changes would bring them in line with where they ought to be in relation to the other casters(clr, shm, enc,nec).<br>
