<br>
The two concepts are largely unrelated and to be honest, the raid issue may never be solved to the satisfaction of most of the high end crowd until EQ2.  Some of the biggest issues in the high end game as far as I can tell are the direct result of very poor long term planning from the start (not the least of which was adding 10 more levels with Kunark).  Many of the more complex issues take far more effort and involve root concepts and strategies of game design.  I foresee many of the more complex high end issues ending up being a main topic of discussion for EQ2 rather then an actual action item in EQ.  A lessons learned sort of thing that would make EQ2 a much better product for all levels.<br>
<br>
I am not really advocating either side, but I have seen what RTFM is talking about quite a bit and agree with his view on it. <p><table border="0">
