 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uoldoaktree.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oldoaktree</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/21/02 4:27:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27390.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> My 2cp...<br>
<br>
I think all caster types should do a better dmg in nukes.  My reasoning is that even wizards lag behind top melee in terms of dmg dealt and caster balance should be addressing that issue--how much do casters overall contribute to the success of a raid and how do we stack up against melee.<br>
<br>
Mages are an odd class.  They get great rains, and some good nukes (about as good as ours).  But what makes them powerful is their pets, and the mage epic pet can do as much dmg on its own as a well geared tank in your guild can.  I am not saying not to up mages dmg ability, but I don't see a pressing need to drop druid nukes to 3rd place since the mages true strength is in the melee its pet does (and that melee can be IMPRESSIVE).  An epic mage with pet up will easily outdamage any wizard...plus mages get at least a few decent clicky nuke items so they continue to have dmg to contribute after their mana is spent (this all assumes you have enough mages that they are not all on mod rod duty).<br>
<br>
I think making all the casters more mana efficient - either by increasing mana pools or reducing nuke mana cost - needs to be the path of caster balance.<br>
<br>
I know different people say different things but overall druids are much more efficient at dealing dmg than at healing, and while we are a priest class, they would need to nearly gut us to suddenly shift that around.  We do need some better heals to put us more in line with other priest classes, but I don't think that should be at the cost of our nuking.  The justification for us being second and third place in several skills, is that we are second place in several.  Letting us fall farther behind on nuking in order to improve but keep us behind on healing will not satisfy me.<br>
<br>
I think the other major issue for caster balance is that the way agro currently works casters have little to do for the first half to two thirds of the fight.  Normally you don't get asked to nuke until the boss mob is at least at half (lower if your guild is cautious).  The risk of landing a big crit nuke and jumping too high up the Hate list and so ruining the whole MA setup can be great.  We need to have a way to be &quot;in the fight&quot; for more of it, rather than standing around waiting for that nuke call.<br>
<br>
I do think all the casters should have spell casting subtlety as a AAXP option--not positive it helps tons but when a druid crit nuke can land for almost 2500dmg (spell casting fury 3 plus mage focus on moonfire, ahve not done the math in detali), I think there is a need.<br>
<br>
Those are my thoughts anyway. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uoldoaktree.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oldoaktree</A> at: 5/21/02 5:04:32 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uronwann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ronwann</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/21/02 4:48:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27390.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> This is kind of an old argument.  For what it's worth I agree with Oak for the most part.  <br>
