 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/21/02 8:14:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27390.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/lag999/rtfm.txt width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Exedor says:  <b><i>Please post your ideas too Keep in mind the purpose is overall caster balance, not just "fixing druids cause we suck" hehe.</b></i><br>
<br>
One of the key imbalances between offensive caster and melee is that melee characters can sustain far higher damage over time due to mana regeneration limitations.<br>
<br>
To fix this problem, either (a) mana regeneration should be increased for all players or (b) druids and wizards should receive an innate ability or "discipline" which has the effect of casting a mana-free direct damage spell, much like the various click-DD items available in game.  In the case of (b), the ability should be calibrated such that one using it alone can achieve a maximum of about 50-75% of the damage of a melee player against a non-resistant target.<br>
<br>
These changes should apply to all players of all levels, but with a particular emphasis on the 50+ crowd where the huge imbalances become manifest. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umissfoxfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miss Foxfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/22/02 5:52:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27390.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gwynhyfar.homestead.com/files/hm9.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> <i>b) druids and wizards should receive an innate ability or "discipline" which has the effect of casting a mana-free direct damage spell, much like the various click-DD items available in game.</i><br>
<br>
That is a darn good idea since we don't get many DD clickies -- the newest clicky DD drops in Vex Thal, so the majority of us have a fat chance of getting one. <br>
